Consent Form

Title of Study: Concept Sourcing for Mental Models: A study of mental models & expertise using a video game context (eIRB#20353)

Principle Investigator: Stacie Sanchez, smsanch2@ncsu.edu, (714) 514-9016

Faculty Point of Contact: Dr. Chris Mayhorn, cbmayhor@ncsu.edu, (919) 513-4856

____________________________________________________________________________________



The purpose of this research study is to gain a better understanding of how people with different levels of expertise organize their knowledge about League of Legends. 



You are being asked to complete a survey and share your League of legends player statistics with the research team for research purposes. Completing this survey is voluntary and you can stop at any time by closing your browser. You also do not need to agree to share you player data to participate in this research. You do not need to give the researchers your summoner name and server you play on if you do not want the research team to have that data. You can leave those questions blank and still participate in this research. However, this information will help the researchers on this project. 



You must be 18 years of age or older to participate in this study, reside in the United States, and have experience playing League of Legends in some form of competitive setting. A competitive setting is defined as having played League of Legends in a competitive matchmaking mode, pick-up games, or through official competitions. 



There are minimal risks associated with your participation in this survey. You will receive $2.00 for completion of this survey. In order to receive full compensation for completing the survey, you must enter a code after completing the survey and pass all attention checks. You will not be compensated more than once. 



If you have any questions about the survey itself, how it is implemented, or survey compensation, please contact the student researcher, Stacie Sanchez, at smsanch2@ncsu.edu or (714) 514-9016, or the faculty advisor for the protocol, Dr. Chris Mayhorn, at cbmayhor@ncsu.edu or (919) 513-4856. Please refer to study number 20353 when contacting someone about this study. 



If you have questions about your rights as a participant or are concerned with your treatment throughout the research process, please contact the NC State University IRB at IRB-Director@ncsu.edu or 1 (919) 515-8754 for help. 

If you consent to complete this survey, please click "I AGREE to participate in this study".
